led in geneva where he raced for the swiss national ski team bteam he studied economics at the university of zurich and at the age of  earned a phd in economics graduating magna cum laude during the s faber worked for white weld  company limited in new york city zurich and hong kong he moved to hong kong in  he was a managing director at drexel burnham lambert ltd hong kong from the beginning of  until the firms collapse in  in  he set up his own business marc faber limited faber now resides in chiang mai thailand though he keeps a small office in hong kong investment viewsedit in sedit faber is credited for advising his clients to get out of the stock market before the october  crash in sedit faber predicted the rise of oil precious metals other commodities emerging markets and especially china in his book tomorrows gold asias age of discovery he stated that there are few value investments available except for farmland and real estate in some emerging markets like russia paraguay and uruguay he also expressed temporary bullishness for the us dollar in mid before it dramatically recovered and positive expectations for holding the japanese yen in december  faber said i think a recovery will not come in the next couple of years maybe in five  years time subsequently the sp  index rose by  from  on january   to  on january   in  faber predicted with full confidence that the federal reserves policy of keeping interest rates near zero would lead to hyperinflation approaching levels seen in zimbabwe subsequently annual increases in the cpi were  in   in   in   in   in   in  and  in  inflation in zimbabwe peaked at  billion percent in midnovember  in sedit in  faber claimed that there was a  chance of a global economic recession later that year or in early  subsequently the average world product grew steadily by  in each of   and  and  in  in  faber predicted that the sp  index would fall at least  within – months following the reelection of barack obama subsequently the sp  index rose from a low of  on november   to  as of january    on april   up  from the november low  months after fabers prediction  on july   up  from the november  low and  on november   up  on march   faber said that the us is creating nowheretohide bubbles in many emerging economies such as indonesia philippines and thailand up four times from  lows on september   faber said we have bubbles everywhere on january   faber predicted that gold prices will rise by  in  gold prices subsequently fell by  from  on january   to  on december   on july   faber stated that investors must hold cash for better buying opportunities after correction writingsedit faber writes the monthly paper investment newsletter the gloom boom  doom report as well as the online subscription letter monthly market commentary he has also authored several books such as the great money illusion the confusion of the confusions  riding the millennial storm marc fabers path to profit in the financial markets  and tomorrows gold asias age of discovery  faber has been a contributor to forbes and international wealth a sister publication of the financial times he has contributed regularly to several websites such as financial intelligence asian bond portal die welt finanzen boerse ame info swiss radio apple hong kong and taiwan quamnet winners wealth and oriental daily he has also written occasionally for the international herald tribune wall street journal and borsa e finanza faber has been long term bearish about the american economy for a number of years and continues to be so he concluded his june  newsletter with the following mock quote the federal government is sending each of us a  rebate if we spend that money at walmart the money goes to china if we spend it on gasoline it goes to the arabs if we buy a computer it will go to india if we purchase fruit and vegetables it will go to mexico honduras and guatemala if we purchase a good car it will go to germany if we purchase useless crap it will go to taiwan and none of it will help the american economy the only way to keep that money here at home is to spend it on prostitutes and beer since these are the only products still produced in us ive been doing my part booksedit tomorrows gold asias age of discovery  riding the millennial storm marc fabers path to profit in the financial markets with mani kiran  the great money illusion the confusion of the confusions  referencesedit  a b c faber marc in whos who of the asian pacific rim volume  pg  published by barons whos who    archived october   at the wayback machine  jessica pressler and bess levin  the fearmongers of finance retrieved    asia frontier capital ltd is a fund management company managing equities in asian frontier countries bangladesh cambodia iraq laos mongolia myanmar pakistan papua new guinea sri lanka vietnam  shareholders asiafrontiercapitalcom retrieved     archived october   at the wayback machine  sterngold james  hong kong empires junk tactic the new york times retrieved     archived september   at the wayback machine  sayson ian c and pimm fox  global markets face severe correction faber says bloomberg archived from the original on  retrieved  cs maint bot originalurl status unknown link  mctague jim  barrons cover dont bet the farm – part ii barrons dow jones retrieved    video  bloomberg business bloombergcom retrieved    mishs global economic trend analysis marc faber  bullish on the us bearish on commodities globaleconomicanalysisblogspotcom  retrieved    marc faber predicts economic disaster in  part  of  youtubecom retrieved    httpwwwmultplcomsphistoricalpricestablebyyear  us inflation to approach zimbabwe level faber says bloombergcom retrieved    httpwwwusinflationcalculatorcominflationconsumerpriceindexandannualpercentchangesfromto  marc faber  chance of global recession cnbccom retrieved    odds of global recession are  marc faber cnbccom retrieved    httpswwwbloombergcomnewsvideosbbabbddebffbbaab  httpwwwmultplcomsphistori